Package com.b2international.snowowl.core.exceptions

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ApiError
    Represents a common error object create because of a failed API call, and can be derived mostly from ApiException subclasses.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApiError.Builder
    Builds ApiError representations.
    ApiValidation  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyExistsException
    Thrown when an item to be created already exists in the system.
    ApiException
    Represents a high-level API call exception.
    BadRequestException
    Thrown when a request contains incorrect parameters or is otherwise malformed.
    ComponentNotFoundException
    Thrown when a terminology component can not be found for a given component identifier.
    ComponentStatusConflictException
    Thrown when a component has been already inactivated in a previous request.
    ConflictException
    Thrown when the same component is modified concurrently by multiple clients, or the request is based on an outdated version of a component.
    CycleDetectedException  
    IllegalQueryParameterException
    Thrown when the supplied query parameters are not acceptable.
    LockedException
    Thrown when a request can not be processed due to a lock existing on the underlying repository.
    MergeConflictException  
    NotFoundException
    Thrown when a requested item could not be found.
    NotImplementedException
    Indicates that some functionality has not been implemented yet.
    RequestTimeoutException  
    SyntaxException
    Generic syntax exception
    ValidationException
